      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions replicate all five COU flow-speed combinations; blood analog fluid properties characterised with uncertainty bounds; temperature controlled to ±0.5 °C.",
      "rationale": "Experimental data covers three of five COU operating points; the two highest-speed points were not tested due to pump availability constraints. Fluid properties were measured at a single temperature without uncertainty quantification. Achieved level 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative metric (e.g., E_rms) applied to hemolysis index predictions vs measurements with uncertainty intervals; systematic bias < 15%.",
      "rationale": "Point-by-point comparison performed at three operating points; E_rms = 28% on hemolysis index. Systematic over-prediction bias of 22% observed at high shear rate conditions. No uncertainty intervals propagated through the comparison metric. Achieved level 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation QoI is the normalised index of hemolysis (NIH) in mg/dL, directly matching the COU decision QoI; no surrogate quantities used.",
      "rationale": "The primary validation QoI is NIH, which matches the COU decision QoI. However, the hemolysis damage model was calibrated against a Couette viscometer dataset rather than a rotating pump geometry, introducing a geometry-relevance gap. Achieved level 3 — QoI matches but calibration basis is partially surrogate."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation activities performed on the FDA generic pump geometry at COU operating conditions; Reynolds number and specific speed within 10% of COU envelope.",
      "rationale": "Validation used the FDA generic pump geometry, which is appropriate, but operating conditions span only 60% of the COU envelope. Two high-flow, high-speed points outside the validated range are extrapolated. Achieved level 2 due to incomplete coverage of the COU operating space."
    },
    {
