      "acceptanceCriteria": "Round-off and iterative convergence errors quantified and shown to be negligible relative to discretization error; residual convergence to 1e-6 for all equations.",
      "rationale": "Solver convergence residuals were monitored but not formally reported against the 1e-6 threshold. Round-off error analysis was not performed. This factor is flagged as an epistemic gap at MRL 5; no evidence package was submitted. Achieved level 1."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Independent review of simulation setup, boundary conditions, and post-processing scripts; checklist-based verification of analyst inputs.",
      "rationale": "No independent review of simulation setup was conducted. Boundary condition assignments and post-processing scripts were prepared by the same analyst without peer check. Flagged as epistemic gap at MRL 5. Achieved level 1."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Turbulence model selection justified by sensitivity study; hemolysis damage model form validated against independent experimental dataset not used in calibration.",
      "rationale": "k-omega SST turbulence model selected without sensitivity comparison against alternative models. The power-law hemolysis model (Giersiepen et al.) was used without validation against an independent dataset; the same Couette data used for calibration was used for validation, constituting circular evidence. Achieved level 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All model input parameters characterised with probability distributions; Monte Carlo or equivalent UQ propagated through hemolysis QoI with reported 95% confidence intervals.",
      "rationale": "Monte Carlo UQ was initiated but only three of eleven uncertain input parameters were assigned distributions (blood viscosity, inlet velocity, rotational speed). Material property uncertainties for the hemolysis model coefficients were not included. Output confidence intervals are therefore underestimated. Achieved level 1."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Minimum of five independent experimental replicates per operating point; inter-sample variability characterised and reported.",
      "rationale": "Only two replicates were performed per operating point due to limited pump availability. Inter-sample variability could not be reliably estimated. Factor flagged as epistemic gap; insufficient sample size to support MRL 5 requirements. Achieved level 1."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Formal mapping between validation experiment input parameters and COU input parameters documented; any discrepancies quantified with sensitivity analysis.",
      "rationale": "No formal equivalency mapping was documented between the validation experiment and the COU. Blood analog fluid (glycerol-water) used in validation differs from clinical blood rheology in the COU; no sensitivity analysis was performed to bound the resulting prediction uncertainty. Flagged as epistemic gap at MRL 5. Achieved level 1."
